hard spheres MD of 
"Packing hard spheres in high dimensional Euclidean spaces", by M. Skoge, A. Donev, F. H. Stillinger, and S. Torquato, 2006


A. Vorontsov (sas@physics.susu.ac.ru ),
South-Ural State University, Chelyabinsk, Russia,

added features:
add Mean Square Displacement for diffusion coeffisient calculations
add Velocity Autocorellation Function (last column in output) 
add maxcycles - maximum number of cycles (if cycling without compression)
add minpf     - minimum packing fraction (if growsrate is negative). It helps if you disorder a crystal.